The paper deals with action recognition and counting in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of deep ConvNets for feature extraction suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and Fourier transform for periodicity mining suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of threshold filters and peak detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep features for action recognition and counting suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
